<http://romanrepublic.ac.uk/rdf/entity/PostAssertionNote/1211> rdfs:label "Post Assertion Note: #1211" ;
	a dprr:PostAssertionNote ;
	dprr:hasSecondarySourceForNote <http://romanrepublic.ac.uk/rdf/entity/SecondarySource/1> ;
	dprr:hasNoteType <http://romanrepublic.ac.uk/rdf/entity/NoteType/1> ;
	dprr:hasNoteText "Fast. Cap. (names entire); Chr. 354; Fast. Hyd.; Chr. Pasc.; Fest. 430 L; Oros. 4.11.10; Cassiod., with Cornelius for Valerius; Zon. 8.18; Degrassi 42f., 117, 438f. Gracchus occupied Sardinia (Fest. 430 L; cf. Polyb. 1.88.8-12; Liv. Per. 20; Zon. 8.18), and campaigned in Liguria, while his colleague engaged the Boii and other Gallic tribes (Oros. 4.12.1; Zon. 8.18; cf. Liv. Per. 20). On Valerius, see Münzer, Gent. Val. 48, no. 41." .
